snippet: Milos Raonic and Vasek Pospisil won their quarterfinal matches Friday, continuing a rare run of success for homegrown players at the Rogers Cup.
abstract: Canadians Milos Raonic and Vasek Pospisil will face each other in Rogers Cup semifinal match, continuing rare run of success for homegrown players at country's biggest tennis event; other tennis news noted.
lead_paragraph: Milos Raonic and Vasek Pospisil won their quarterfinal matches Friday, continuing a rare run of success for homegrown players at the Rogers Cup.
